commit.message:
allocator: properly handle overflow when large number of surfaces imported (#6550)

- Fixed specific corner case when user import more than 2^16 surfaces and keep some of them.
  Now checking new mid if it not belongs to already existing surface.
  This became possible after adding Import flow for surfaces creation.

- Added ULT to cover such scenario

commit.message:
[RT Common] Enable binary build for revenue platforms (#6523)

Currently one-VPL build will build out VPL binaries for all supported
platforms including future platforms. That's why some IP leaks were
detected in VPL binaries on revenue platforms. This PR is intented to
create a release-revenue build type in which VPL code for future
platforms won't be built out through option control in makefiles and
same macro control in shared source code.

Co-authored-by: Yuan, Jenny <jenny.yuan@intel.com>
